name: Durgod Fusion Retro Keyboard (Navigator)
review: I am not a fan. There are pings everywhere on the board and it just doesn't live up to the price tag.

name: Ajazz AK816 Pro 75% Gasket Hot-Swappable Bluetooth
review: Another smooth keyboard that is slightly overpriced. The keyboard is nice, but the accessories that it comes with feel cheap and junky.

name: Alienware Low Profile RGB Mechanical Gaming Keyboard
review: I personally like this keyboard because it's uniquely designed so that you can easily tell that it's made by Alienware at the first glance. Low profile MX red is not my favourite though.

name: Logitech Wireless Keyboard K400 Plus
review: The keypress is not great, but it's definitely the best budget TV keyboard that I can easily recommend.

name: Logitech K750 Wireless Solar Keyboard for Mac
review: I'm in love with the keypress. It feels really nice in my opinion. The hardware is not built to last though but I find this a very comfortable keyboard to type on.

name: Logitech MX Keys Mini for Mac
review: This is another bluetooth-only keyboard from Logitech. The keypress feels amazing and the connection is solid as well, but it only has 3 stars because it doesn't support wired mode! A USB-C to USB-C cable is provided, but it can only be used to charge the keyboard and not for connection.

name: Logitech K380 Multi-Device Bluetooth Keyboard for Mac - Rose
review: This is a bluetooth-only keyboard. It's passable for the price. The connection is solid, but I personally don't like bluetooth and am not a fan of these keycaps.

name: MSI Vigor GK71 Sonic Mechanical Gaming Keyboard
review: This is an okay keyboard. They advertised too much on the MSI Sonic Red switch. In reality, it's just an Outemu red which is kind of disappointing. Otherwise the control knob is good and also comes with a wrist rest.

name: Apple Magic Keyboard
review: It is a membrane keyboard but I love this one! ❤

name: Yunzii KC68
review: An awesome keyboard. However, 65% keyboard is a bit too small for my daily usage, but great typing experience for me!

name: Shurikey Gear Hanzo 65%
review: This keyboard looks great, but there is a problem with wired mode that it doesn't stay connected and failed as being a keyboard. 5 out of 5 for looks though. It's a deocrated piece and nothing more.

name: HyperX Origins Core
review: I love this keyboard. The typing experience feels super butter smooth!

name: ASUS ROG Claymore Core
review: This is the first version of claymore core. It was already a legacy product when I get into the keyboard world. It's a TKL keyboard, but you can purchase the numberpad separately and you can connect it either to the right or left side of the keyboard. The idea sounds really cool, but I didn't have the numberpad to play around.

name: Razer Blackwidow Lite
review: I'm not a fan of tactile switches, but this one is actually pretty solid after all the comparison against some other worse ones. I did a review on the mercury version, but I ended up keeping the stormtrooper one.

name: Corsair K65 2020 Limited Bundle
review: The keyboard is just ok, but the mouse and the mousepad are pretty nice

name: James Donkey K619
review: My very first mechanical keyboard. It was somewhere around $40. I wanted a keyboard that has the same yellow as this site. It does not have RGB and only has the orange-yellow backlight, but it's perfect for me 💛
